@{
	ViewBag.Title = "Requirements";
}
<p>
<font face="Liberation Sans, sans-serif">
	<font size="6" style="font-size: 28pt">
		<b>
			NASA
			Mars Rover Movement Program (RoverPath)
		</b>
	</font>
</font></p>
<h1 class="western">Overview</h1>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
	NASA will be sending
	two rovers to Mars. A program is needed to test the rovers&rsquo;
	movements.
</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
	<br />

</p>
<h2 class="western">Information</h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			The movement
			grid is laid out as an (x, y) coordinate system, with the origin (0,
			0) representing the southwest corner.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			The current
			rover position is indicated by an (x, y, z) coordinate system,
			relative to the grid origin, (0, 0).
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
					x = horizontal
					position
				</p>
			<li>
				<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
					y = vertical
					position
				</p>
			<li>
				<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
					z = current
					heading (N, S, E, W)
				</p>
		</ul>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Acceptable
			movement instructions are single characters.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
					L = turn 90
					degrees left (counter clockwise)
				</p>
			<li>
				<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
					R = turn 90
					degrees right (clockwise)
				</p>
			<li>
				<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
					M = move 1
					grid space forward in current heading
				</p>
				<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%"></p>
		</ul>
</ul>
<h2 class="western">Requirements</h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Accept the grid
			size and each rover&rsquo;s current position and movement
			instructions, one line per input item (see Inputs section, below).
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Output updated
			rover (x, y, z) position for each rover.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Rover 2 may not
			move until rover 1 has completed its sequence successfully.
		</p>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%"></p>
</ul>
<h2 class="western">Assumptions</h2>
<ul>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			There are only
			two rovers.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			A movement
			sequence can be sent for only 1 rover. For example, rover 1 can
			receive instructions while rover 2 receives none, and vice versa.
			However, the current position and heading for both rovers are always
			required.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			The movement
			sequence through the grid has been verified to be free of known
			obstacles. For example, the sequence would not intentionally take a
			rover over a cliff.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Unknown
			obstacle detection and avoidance are handled by a different program.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Movement
			outside the input grid area is not allowed.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Even if its
			sequence is valid, rover 2 cannot move if rover 1 has an invalid
			sequence or encounters an error.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			The 2 rovers
			cannot occupy the same grid space at the same time.
		</p>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			The grid area
			can be rectangular or square, as long as it includes the current
			positions of each rover.
		</p>
</ul>
<h2 class="western">Inputs</h2>
<ol>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Grid size as
			represented by the (x, y) coordinates of the north east corner.
			Required, values only, separated with a space.
		</p>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">Example: 5 5</p>
</ul>
<ol start="2">
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Current
			position and heading of rover 1 as represented by the (x, y, z)
			coordinates. Required,  values only, separated with a space.
		</p>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">Example: 1 2 N</p>
</ul>
<ol start="3">
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Movement
			sequence of rover 1. Values only, no spaces, all caps.
		</p>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Example:
			LMLMLMLMM
		</p>
</ul>
<ol start="4">
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Current
			position and heading of rover 2 as represented by the (x, y, z)
			coordinates. Required,  values only, separated with a space.
		</p>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">Example: 3 3 E</p>
</ul>
<ol start="5">
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Movement
			sequence of rover 2. Values only, no spaces, all caps.
		</p>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Example:
			MMRMMRMRRM
		</p>
</ul>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
	<br />

</p>
<h2 class="western">Outputs</h2>
<ol>
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Updated
			position and heading of rover 1 as represented by the (x, y, z)
			coordinates. Values only, separated with a space.
		</p>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">Example: 1 3 N</p>
</ul>
<ol start="2">
	<li>
		<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">
			Updated
			position and heading of rover 2 as represented by the (x, y, z)
			coordinates. Values only, separated with a space.
		</p>
</ol>
<ul>
	<li><p style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 100%">Example: 5 1 E</p>
</ul>